BEFORE/AFTER: log 13 (semantic-only, all-minilm) topped out at `diff` and
`not_found_error` — plausible-but-wrong. The hybrid pulls the actual
incremental-refresh / staleness symbol to #1, because BM25 rewards the exact
topic terms ("incremental", "re-parsing", "change") that the general embedding
model blurred. This is the "similar != relevant" fix the lexical arm exists for.

